results.name: Permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A083221(A255552(n)).
comment: a(n) tells which number in array A083221, constructed from the sieve of Eratosthenes is at the same position where n is in array A255551 constructed from Lucky sieve. As both arrays have A005843 (even numbers) as their topmost row, this permutation fixes all of them.
